{
  "text": "In our study, those who never brushed their teeth stated that their OHRQoL was affected by psychological discomfort (OHIP-14 subdomain), Dahl et al. [CITATION_1] evaluated the correlation between the tooth brushing frequency and the OHRQoL using the OHIP-14 scale among 3,538 individuals, and they reported that individuals who used toothpicks on a daily basis had better oral hygiene and OHRQoL.",
